headline: Jimmy Cliff, the singer who brought reggae beyond Jamaica, has died at age 81
description: From 'Many Rivers to Cross' in 1969 to 'Reggae Night' in 1983, Cliff served as an ambassador for ska and reggae before the genre's icon, Bob Marley. Cliff died on November 24 at the age of 81.

headline: Why Grok is first and foremost a disinformation machine
description: Grok, the chatbot that has been integrated into the X social network and aims to rival ChatGPT, has recently spread Holocaust denial and false information about the November 2015 attacks in France. It was a reminder that Elon Musk's tool, far from being neutral, was designed to misinform.

description: Niklas Frank, an 86-year-old former journalist, is known in Germany for his absolute loathing of his father. As a Reich official, Hans Frank, appointed by Hitler in Poland, was among those sentenced to death at the Nuremberg trials, which began 80 years ago.

headline: François Hollande: 'Trump's plan reduces Europe's role to a besieged bystander'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the former French president argued that 'for Trump, our continent is finished, it no longer counts,' and warned that if Zelensky 'falls, it is our own security that will be compromised. Sooner or later, we too will fall.'
